Here is the cleaned up text:

Generate a Salesforce Report for Amazon Connect Usage and Billing

View your Salesforce org’s Amazon Connect usage, minutes, and costs, and Amazon Lex usage with Salesforce reports. Create a custom report type and then generate a report on your Salesforce org’s usage.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
To create custom report types:	Create and Customize Reports AND Manage Custom Report Types
To delete custom report types:	Create and Customize Reports AND Manage Custom Report Type AND Modify All Data
To create, edit, and delete reports in private folders:	Create and Customize Reports
To create, edit, and delete reports in public and private folders:	Report Builder (Lightning Experience

Create a custom report type for your org’s Amazon Connect usage.
From Setup, enter Report Types in the Quick Find box, then select Report Types.
Click New Custom Report Type.
Select Service Cloud Voice Usage and Cost to report on Amazon Connect usage and costs.
Select Service Cloud Voice Minutes to report on Amazon Connect metrics.
Select Service Cloud IVR to report on Amazon Lex metrics.

Enter the Report Type Label and the Report Type Name.
Enter a description for your custom report type, up to 255 characters long.
For the Category, select Other Reports.
For the Deployment Status, select Deployed.
Click Next.
Save your work.

Build the report in Lightning Report Builder.
Add fields to your report as columns, group rows columns, filter the report data, and show or hide charts. Customize your report until it shows exactly the data that you need.
Filter the report by Billed AWS Service, Usage Month, and Usage Year fields to view monthly AWS services and billing charges.

When you save your work, give your report a name and a description.
To view report results, click Run.
title: Generating Salesforce Reports for Amazon Connect Usage and Billing
